      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Classic Scrabble Board</h2>

      <p>The classic board is what most people picture when they think of Scrabble. It is affordable, widely available, and comes complete with everything needed to play.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Pros</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Affordable ($20–$30). Complete set included. Lightweight. Familiar feel. Available everywhere. Good for families and casual play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Cons</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles slide easily. Flat board difficult for 4 players. Plastic tiles feel cheap. Board warps over time. No tile-locking mechanism.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Best for: families with children, occasional players, anyone who wants a complete set at the lowest price. Not recommended for regular game night hosts or competitive players who find sliding tiles frustrating.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Deluxe Rotating Board</h2>

      <p>The deluxe board solves every problem with the classic. The rotating base means no one has to read the board upside-down, and the raised grid keeps tiles locked in place throughout the game.</p>

