        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Materials:</span> Look for weather-treated wood or durable plastic. Cheaper sets use foam tiles that blow away in wind. Weighted wooden tiles are worth the premium.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Storage:</span> These sets are bulky. Make sure you have garage or shed space. A mesh bag for tiles and a flat spot for the board are essential.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Vintage & Collector Boards</h2>

      <p>For the Scrabble enthusiast who has everything, vintage editions offer nostalgia and craftsmanship. These range from 1950s originals to modern luxury reproductions.</p>

